
[1]disadvantage

   DISADVANTAGE, n.

   1. That which prevents success, or renders it difficult; a state not
   favorable to successful operation. The army commenced an attack on the
   enemy, notwithstanding the disadvantage of its position.

   2. Any unfavorable state; a state in which some loss or injury may be
   sustained. Hence,

   3. Loss; injury; prejudice to interest, fame, credit, profit, or other
   good; as, to sell goods to disadvantage.

           DISADVANTAGE, v.t. To injure in interest; to prejudice.
